methods.addChunk:
Aggregate a chunk of data into the result columns.

*Overload 1*  
  :param context: (io.deephaven.db.v2.by.IterativeChunkedAggregationOperator.BucketedContext) - the operator-specific context
  :param values: (io.deephaven.db.v2.sources.chunk.Chunk<? extendsio.deephaven.db.v2.sources.chunk.Attributes.Values>) - a chunk of values to aggregate
  :param inputIndices: (io.deephaven.db.v2.sources.chunk.LongChunk<? extendsio.deephaven.db.v2.sources.chunk.Attributes.KeyIndices>) - the input indices, in post-shift space
  :param destinations: (io.deephaven.db.v2.sources.chunk.IntChunk<io.deephaven.db.v2.sources.chunk.Attributes.KeyIndices>) - the destinations in resultColumn to aggregate into, parallel with startPositions and length
  :param startPositions: (io.deephaven.db.v2.sources.chunk.IntChunk<io.deephaven.db.v2.sources.chunk.Attributes.ChunkPositions>) - the starting positions in the chunk for each destination
  :param length: (io.deephaven.db.v2.sources.chunk.IntChunk<io.deephaven.db.v2.sources.chunk.Attributes.ChunkLengths>) - the number of values in the chunk for each destination
  :param stateModified: (io.deephaven.db.v2.sources.chunk.WritableBooleanChunk<io.deephaven.db.v2.sources.chunk.Attributes.Values>) - a boolean output array, parallel to destinations, which is set to true if the corresponding
          destination has been modified
  
*Overload 2*  
  :param context: (io.deephaven.db.v2.by.IterativeChunkedAggregationOperator.SingletonContext) - the operator-specific context
  :param chunkSize: (int) - the size of the addition
  :param values: (io.deephaven.db.v2.sources.chunk.Chunk<? extendsio.deephaven.db.v2.sources.chunk.Attributes.Values>) - the values to aggregate
  :param inputIndices: (io.deephaven.db.v2.sources.chunk.LongChunk<? extendsio.deephaven.db.v2.sources.chunk.Attributes.KeyIndices>) - the input indices, in post-shift space
  :param destination: (long) - the destination in the result columns
  :return: (boolean) true if the state was modified, false otherwise
methods.ensureCapacity:
Ensure that this operator can handle destinations up to tableSize - 1.

:param tableSize: (long) - the new size of the table
methods.getResultColumns:
Return a map of result columns produced by this operator.

:return: (java.util.Map<java.lang.String,? extends io.deephaven.db.v2.sources.ColumnSource<?>>) a map of name to columns for the result table
methods.removeChunk:
Remove a chunk of data previously aggregated into the result columns.

*Overload 1*  
  :param context: (io.deephaven.db.v2.by.IterativeChunkedAggregationOperator.BucketedContext) - the operator-specific context
  :param values: (io.deephaven.db.v2.sources.chunk.Chunk<? extendsio.deephaven.db.v2.sources.chunk.Attributes.Values>) - a chunk of values that have been previously aggregated.
  :param inputIndices: (io.deephaven.db.v2.sources.chunk.LongChunk<? extendsio.deephaven.db.v2.sources.chunk.Attributes.KeyIndices>) - the input indices, in pre-shift space
  :param destinations: (io.deephaven.db.v2.sources.chunk.IntChunk<io.deephaven.db.v2.sources.chunk.Attributes.KeyIndices>) - the destinations in resultColumn to remove the values from, parallel with startPositions and
          length
  :param startPositions: (io.deephaven.db.v2.sources.chunk.IntChunk<io.deephaven.db.v2.sources.chunk.Attributes.ChunkPositions>) - the starting positions in the chunk for each destination
  :param length: (io.deephaven.db.v2.sources.chunk.IntChunk<io.deephaven.db.v2.sources.chunk.Attributes.ChunkLengths>) - the number of values in the chunk for each destination
  :param stateModified: (io.deephaven.db.v2.sources.chunk.WritableBooleanChunk<io.deephaven.db.v2.sources.chunk.Attributes.Values>) - a boolean output array, parallel to destinations, which is set to true if the corresponding
          destination has been modified
  
*Overload 2*  
  :param context: (io.deephaven.db.v2.by.IterativeChunkedAggregationOperator.SingletonContext) - the operator-specific context
  :param chunkSize: (int) - the size of the removal
  :param values: (io.deephaven.db.v2.sources.chunk.Chunk<? extendsio.deephaven.db.v2.sources.chunk.Attributes.Values>) - the values to remove from the aggregation
  :param inputIndices: (io.deephaven.db.v2.sources.chunk.LongChunk<? extendsio.deephaven.db.v2.sources.chunk.Attributes.KeyIndices>) - the input indices, in pre-shift space
  :param destination: (long) - the destination in the result columns
  :return: (boolean) true if the state was modified, false otherwise
methods.startTrackingPrevValues: Called after initialization; when the operator's result columns must have previous tracking enabled.
